.TH "ntfs_file_write_iter" 9 "ntfs_file_write_iter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ntfs_file_write_iter \- simple wrapper for ntfs_file_write_iter_nolock()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" ntfs_file_write_iter
.BI "(struct kiocb *iocb "  ","
.BI "struct iov_iter *from "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "iocb" 12
IO state structure
.IP "from" 12
iov_iter with data to write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Basically the same as \fBgeneric_file_write_iter\fP except that it ends up
up calling \fBntfs_perform_write\fP instead of \fBgeneric_perform_write\fP and that
O_DIRECT is not implemented.
